      <h3>What do you learn?</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="col-12">
      <p>
        During 3 days retreat participants will learn how to meditate in a peaceful environment with a Buddhist monk.
        Meditation technique is The Middle Way, known as Dhammakaya technique in Thailand. This technique emphasis is
        on comfort. Within a comfortable environment people’s mind can become really calm and peaceful.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-12">
      <p>
        General session will be with teaching and meditation practice. Coaching can be also given during the session
        or at personal request to guide and tune the mind effectively. Participants are encouraged to ask questions
        concerning meditation, how to apply into everyday life and Buddhism from teaching monks.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-12">
      <p>
        It’s a balance between spiritual self discipline to practice oneself, wake up early, take two meals a day and
        comfort of accommodation, nature, food and meditation technique.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-12">
      <h3>Overview</h3>
      <p>
        People with any religious backgrounds (or none) are welcomed at our retreat. The minimum age requirement is
        18. We request that all participants be in a good state of health and comfortable in rustic surroundings with
        a genuine desire to learn and practice meditation in our established program. All participants are requested
        to abstain from smoking or drinking alcohol and take two meals a day to support your meditation practice. The
        Meditation Retreat is run by a Buddhist Charity based in the UK which promotes world peace through inner
        peace.
      </p>
